definition.value: A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-alanine in which one of the methyl hydrogens is replaced by a 5-tert-butyl-3-hydroxy-isooxazol-4-yl group.

Prostaglandin F2alpha in which the hydrogen at position 15 is substituted by methyl (S configuration). It is used as an abortifacient agent that is effective in both the first and second trimesters of pregnancy.
A member of the class of chloroethenes that is ethene in which both of the hydrogens attached to one of the carbons are replaced by chlorines.
A benzoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of benzoic acid with tert-butanol.
A trimethylbenzene carrying methyl groups at positions 1, 2 and 3. It has been found in  Centaurium erythraea.
A trimethylbenzene carrying methyl groups at positions 1, 2 and 4.
The tromethamine salt of carboprost. It is used as an abortifacient agent that is effective in both the first and second trimesters of pregnancy.
A phenylenediamine in which the two amino groups are ortho to each other.
A CDP-diacylglycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as dodecanoyl.
A diphenylethane that is the 1,2-dihydro derivative of stilbene.

An anilide obtained by formal condensation of the amino group of aniline with the carboxy group of 2-methyl-5,6-dihydro-1,4-oxathiine-3-carboxylic acid. A fungicide for control of bunts and smuts that is normally used as a seed treatment.
A dimethylnaphthalene carrying methyl groups at positions 1 and 2.
